          <p style="margin-bottom: 50px; font-size: 20px;">
            This endpoint will fetch one random song that matches query. Endpoint must contain at least one
            query.
          </p>
          <p style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 16px; max-width: 600px;'><u>Valid queries</u> <br>Below are all the
            queries that can be used in the url. Any query used other than
            the
            ones indicated below will
            result in a 400 response code.</p>

          <ul style='margin-bottom: 25px;'>
            <li>
              <h4>
                <code style="color: rgb(218, 70, 143); font-weight: bold;">?artist</code>
              </h4>
            </li>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">This will filter requests by artist</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">Artist query must be all lowercase with no special characters</p>
              </li>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p style="display: inline;">Dr. Dre = drdre</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p style="display: inline;">Jay-Z = jayz</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p style="display: inline;">Andre 3000 = andre3000</p>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">example: <a href='/api/filter?artist=jayz' style='text-decoration: none;'><code class="text-secondary">/api/filter?artist=jayz</code></a></p>

              </li>
            </ul>
            <li>
              <h4>
                <code style="color: rgb(218, 70, 143); font-weight: bold;">?explicit</code>
              </h4>
            </li>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">Returns lyrics that either contain explicit language or not</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">Can only be true or false</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">example: <a href='/api/filter?explicit=false' style='text-decoration: none;'><code class="text-secondary">/api/filter?explicit=false</code></a></p>

              </li>
            </ul>
            <li>
              <h4>
                <code style="color: rgb(218, 70, 143); font-weight: bold;">?year</code>
              </h4>
            </li>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">Will filter out lyrics by year it came out</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">Value is in year format, do not need month or day</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p style="display: inline;">example: <a href='/api/filter?year=1985' style='text-decoration: none;'><code class="text-secondary">/api/filter?year=1985</code></a></p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </ul>

          <p style="max-width: 550px;">Keep in mind all filter
            queries can be used at once. Different combinations can
            get back unique results. Fetching non-explicit song lyrics from Jay-Z in the year 2012 would be <a href='/api/filter?artist=jayz&explicit=false&year=2012'>/api/filter?artist=jayz&explicit=false&year=2012</a>
          </p>




